FASTEST METHOD-

1. Place beans and water (at least 2 or 3 inches of water above beans) in pressure
cooker along with 1 or 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil. Cook under high pressure 
or 5 minutes. Remove from heat and allow pressure to release naturally. 

2. Drain and discard water, rinse beans.

3, Cook under high pressure for the desired time.

SECOND FASTEST METHOD -

1. Place beans and water in pressure cooker. Boil water and beans for 3 minutes.

2. Remove from heat, cover and allow to sit for two hours.

3. Drain, rinse beans and then pressure cook for desired time.

